<br>
Yes and no.  The nature of the beast is that chaining is a low aggro activity.  Slow is generally a much higher aggro, and thus needs to be overcome with each new pet.<br>
<br>
These are the things that help chainers (both regular and IR breeds):<br>
<br>
1.  Improvements in innate pet attributes, including average and max hits, resists, hit points, ac, innate delay, level, procs or spells<br>
<br>
2.  Buffs that are relatively quick to cast, encompass several pet attributes, and cost relatively little mana<br>
<br>
3.  Mana efficiency skills and effects<br>
<br>
4.  Increases in mana regen<br>
<br>
These are things that help non-chainers:<br>
<br>
1.  1,2,3,4 above<br>
<br>
2.  Weapons and armor, summoned or cheaply replaceable<br>
<br>
3.  Improvements in heal spells, in number of hit points healed, efficiency, and cast time<br>
<br>
4.  Improvements in direct damage spells, in number of hit points healed, efficiency, cast time, and resist rates<br>
<br>
<br>
It looks to me that chainers require fewer kinds of improvements to be happy, and any improvements made to chaining also benefits non-chainers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Do you see any other class having to make up tricks to do something they did at lower levels without tricks?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't understand what you mean.  If you mean that chaining pets is a high level &quot;trick&quot;, then you have to realize that chaining is doable but a bit less viable at lower levels simply because of the relative mana cost of pets vs. mana pool and innate mana regen.  Chaining gets better with level, just like quadding for Wizards and Druids, or root dotting for Necromancers, Druids, and Shaman.<br>
<br>
Chaining is a tactic that is uniquely &quot;Magician,&quot; especially IR chaining.  No other class can do what we do resummoning pets.  Why deny the summoning side of us?  If we can explore our evocation side in PoP groups, there's nothing wrong with improving the conjuration side of us in solo or in nontraditional groups.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>However, if the Magician class was done right there would be no reason to chain cast. Did you start the class by chain casting...NO. Back in Kunark did people chain cast...NO. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If the magician class were done &quot;right&quot; it would create class  balance issues.  We are at the core a balanced group by ourselves, with aspects of tank, healer, damage dealer.  The only thing we really lack is crowd control.  Did I start the class by chain casting?  No, because I had no clue how to do it.  Believe me, I tried.  Once I learned, I never went back.  Did people chain pets in Kunark?  Actually, they did.  Way back all the Voc and G Voc pets cost 200 mana, just like the 29-49 pets did.  Increasing the mana cost was a response to chaining, as it seemed a bit too efficient for the content. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1290<br> <font color=#333333>(11/23/02 11:40:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Supplement to Chain Casting - New spell</span><hr size=1> I really don't care either way on chaining. I have chained pets more so after the release of focus items that reduce mana cost and reduce casting speed on pets. Anyway I see it from both sides. VI is never going to make pets as strong as they should be because we can pump them out so easy. I do think that our pets should have had a few more hps but with suspend menion that is pretty much the answer to that. If one pet dies just pop the other one out that you have suspended. <br>
<br>
I never cared for chain casting because personally it is to slow for my taste. It really requires velious robe/pants to be done well. Without those then the mana savings isn't really all that good. We have highend nukes now that are very good and have the conjuration check. So you are saving very little by chaining while increasing the risk to yourself. I personally prefer to group now, because experience moves much faster then solo. I soloed because it was faster way to get experience, now that isn't the case so i don't do it much.  <br>
<br>
I think people need to really stop thinking in terms of POP. NO ONE can tank well in PoP, and very few classes can solo well. Slow is needed for melee to tank or they get chewed to little pieces. Also pets gained about 700 additional hps in this expansion, and then another 600 from the summoned weapons and the girlde. Also pet mitigation is very high in this expansion. If you don't think so take your air pet to UP and put it up against the dark blue mobs there and you will see. The air and water pet tank very well. POP was not suppose to be a solo expansion and just look at all the ways they have been nerfing druid/wizard/bard solo ability.<br>
<br>
Yes my pets get chewed up in PoP but honestly they do better then a larger percentage of melee that are not insanely uber. See how long a monk or rogue can tank the golems in PoV unslowed, or for that case a warrior or paladin. Our pets are fine i really don't know what people want. If lvl 65 warriors get chewed in about 12 to 15secs to a golem in PoV why should our pets be any different.<br>
<br>
In closing this spell idea is a waste of time. Only the earth pet would have remotely the amount of hps for this spell to be even useful, and why add one spell for one pet that the majority of mages are never going to have.  The Dev team isn't going to add any spell that allows us to solo better in the planes. It just isn't going to happen because they don't want people soloing at all in the planes. This spell isn't needed outside of the planes because we solo just fine in those areas.<br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1157<br> <font color=#333333>(11/23/02 5:50:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Supplement to Chain Casting - New spell</span><hr size=1> I really dont want this thread to be about arguing about chaincasting ethics... Yes our pets die quickly in PoP, and maybe verant doesnt like soloing.. However until Verant changes Charm soloing so that chanters dont get 5aa in less than 4 hours I honestly see them as hypocrits therefore they *want* classes to solo well, and mages have always been a solo class... So we should have the option along with necros, wizards, druids and chanters <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
